name: Hike up to sunrise
description: Although I have been going to the Tatra Mountains for more than 10 years, until now I have never been there alone. My dream was to go to the West Tatra Mountains alone. After 3 a.m., at the beginning of September, I set off from the shelter on Polana Chochołowska towards Wołowiec. Several hours of climbing in absolute darkness was a new and strange feeling for me. I was both excited and slightly anxious. Above me I could see the starry sky, which is impossible to observe in urban surroundings. The stars were bright and clear, and even larger star clusters were discernible. I had an overwhelming urge to stare at the sky longer, but I had an ambitious goal… sunrise. As I emerged above the forest line, a colourful glow of light appeared in the sky. The sun was about to appear closer to the horizon line.
